OL,6,FIn court, Mr Justice Pepperall said:
OL,7,F"This was a sustained and vicious
OL,8,Fattack and you showed no mercy with a
OL,9,Fknife, a bottle which was used to
OL,10,Fbludgeon him and caused serious head
OL,11,Finjuries and your shoes caused rib
OL,12,Ffractures.
OL,14,F"It's sadly clear from arms and
OL,15,Fbruising that Mr Wilcox suffered as he
OL,16,Fbravely sought to defend himself
OL,17,Fbefore he lost consciousness and died.
OL,19,F"It was a murder committed at least
OL,20,Fpartly in anger as Mr Wilcox no longer
OL,21,Fhad funds.
