OL,4,Cmurder of 'much-loved' grandfather
OL,6,F"I hope this lengthy sentence gives
OL,7,Fthem both some time to reflect on what
OL,8,Fthey have done."
OL,10,FMr Wilcox's family said: "Mark loved
OL,11,Fus all and we loved him. We have lost
OL,12,Four loving, funny, kind, and sensitive
OL,13,Fbrother, son, husband, uncle, father,
OL,14,Fgrandfather, mentor, and friend.
OL,16,F"Mark was a kind, caring and generous
OL,17,Fman who made us smile and laugh and
OL,18,Fwhom always had a kind word for
OL,19,Feveryone he met and knew.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G10/11
